body:
SUMMARY OF THE POSITION: 
Participate for the Applicative Solutions group in the administration of Microsoft SQL databases required by projects or support / maintenance activities.

Responsibilities:

•Advise users in defining their needs (processes and systems);
•Approve data models and tables produced by other technical resources;
•Advise developers on techniques used to achieve better performance and work together with them in SQL query rewrite as needed;
•Migrate BD components in development environments, integrated testing, pre-production and production;
•Special Back-up/Restore requested by the development team in the development and pre-production environments;
•Optimize application performance  by adding required indexes, doing re-indexation of BD, identifying non performing SQL procedure and recommending optimizations, etc.;
•Manage access rights to the DB;
•Participate in the evaluation, design and / or acquisition as well as the implementation of new applications or major improvements to existing business applications.

Qualifications & Experience:

•Bachelor Degree in computer science and more than 3 years of experience;
•Experience in technical support to development teams (required)
•Thorough knowledge of T-SQL (required)
•Excellent ability in performance tuning (SQL best practices, data modeling and indexing) (required)
•Experience with Informatica ETL tool (Asset)
•Good knowledge of data modeling (Asset)

Capabilities:
•Proficiency in English (French writing and speaking is an advantage); 
•Attention to detail and thoroughness;
•Customer service oriented;
•Ability to work well in a team environment.

We offer: 
•A friendly and professional working environment;
•Opportunities to learn and grow in a multi-national company.
